				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know a little about this, Tink, but you should keep asking around. I'm not the most-informed source on MB.
<br />

<br />
The basic strat as it was told to me: You kill the spiders in the MB's area until the MB becomes active and can be targeted, then you mezz all the spiders and send in the MT to gain aggro, then you have everyone attack. MGB HoT heals during the fight help the raid survive the AEs.  When you kill him LEAVE THE ROOM IMMEDIATELY and get corpses dragged out ASAP (rogues with SoS if possible) to the hallways to rez.  The gnome that you hail despawns fairly quickly after the kill, 15 min I believe.
<br />

<br />
One key to winning - DO NOT have folks under level 60 fight him. Period.  They are just guaranteed to pingpong him and wipe the raid. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />  He will also switch targets due to low health aggro if the fight goes on too long.
<br />

<br />
At least one of the MB's AE's is a lure, meaning it cannot be resisted if you are in range, just FYI.
<br />

<br />
Try to have a bard in the MT's group singing the uber resist song RIGHT on the MT's feet.  Will help him with the non-lure AEs.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
1. The best way to handle the spiders I have seen (this is AFTER the MB "awakens" and you engage him) is to keep all the spiders mezzed.  Need a minimum of 4 enchanters for this, 1 in each corner outside the MB's room.
<br />

<br />
2. Don't believe the MB can be manadrained.  But this is literally a 60 second fight, really no time to drain him anyway.
<br />

<br />
3. Clerics can heal from outside the MB's AE range if he is pulled into a corner... however, the way I've done it, we didn't worry about the AE, since the fight is VERY short.  We just stood in the doorways and healed. If you have 3 clerics with MGB, you can have them MGB Ethereal Elixir at 100%, 75% and 50% of MB's health and it will help a ton to keep the raid alive.
<br />

<br />
4. Dunno if there is a map for it.
<br />

<br />
5. I think the MB can summon.  
<br />

<br />
6. Only the 72 folks in the raid can get the flag now, as far as I know.
<br />

<br />
7. Spiders are, I think, immune to changes in their runspeed, so no root or snare.  MB drops so fast that you don't need the chanters trying to charm and add risk that way - they are better off just mezzing everything.
<br />

<br />
8. Warrior makes your best tank for him (defensive disc).
<br />

<br />
9. I'm not sure on the MB's hitpoints, but believe me when I say that the fight (with a really good raid force, mind you) took literally 60 seconds. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Hope that helps a little.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=593087" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Tryllium Calaquendi</span></a>
<br />
Archon of Utter Hootchieness</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
