			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">On the intial Behemo engage it can be very helpful to have a Ranger stand on one side of the room and snare him as soon as he spawns and pop weaponshield.  This gives you 18 seconds to get your melee on one side of the room and casters on the other.  By doing so Clerics can spam heal SR and never get hit by the AE and nukers can cast freely avoiding the AE.  We normally just use 1 group at each door to CC with 2 chanters 1 covering each direction a shaman, a druid for heals and a tank to keepone aggroed so none race into the room.  As soon as MB dies the druids evac and those 2 groups clear back in real fast.  Most raids are able to drop MB because of his complete lack of HPs but die right after.  You need to exit the room asap.  No one touches any spiders no bards play any songs no one heals the morons that attack the spiders.  On CR be patient watch the spiders wait for them to go in and explode and you can run in grab a corpse or 2 pause and wait repeat.  If your inside the doors the AE will nail you.
<br />

<br />
For a tank you will have the same problem Alarius did the first time we did him and not have warriors with good taunt weapons.  It is best to use an SK or paladin on him to keep your nukers from getting aggro.  Lightening reflexs 5 and most hps and if you have an SK with the 7k HT that is solid aggro.  SK's with the big HT will alos help immensly in dropping his hps very very quickly.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103522" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nurbok Wildflower</a>
<br />
Tianni's Chubby Hubby
<br />
<a href="http://www.alariusofbrell.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Guildleader of Alarius</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
